{"title":"The New Leatherman Curl Multi-Tool includes the option for replaceable bits","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/08/20/leatherman-curl-multi-tool-plus-bit-kit/","date":1629463648000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Leatherman just launched its latest addition to a long, proud line of multi-tools with its new 15-in-1 Curl. It’s 4 inches and 7 ounces of 100% stainless steel utility. And, sure, that’s a lot of power in a compact package, but that’s not where it stops. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/08/28/found-leatherman-charge-tti-is-the-titanium-multi-tool-wed-carry-for-trail-and-trailside-repairs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Leatherman</a> engineered the Curl with what it calls “bit kit compatibility.” Leatherman-style multi-tools can be very handy in addition to your bike multi-tools, but typically haven’t worked well as a replacement. This may change that.</p><p>Let’s dive into the specs.</p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/images.gearjunkie.com/uploads/2021/08/LTG_CURL_OutdoorFishing_18.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x322/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" alt=\"Leatherman Curl scissors\" width=\"3000\" height=\"1996\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/images.gearjunkie.com/uploads/2021/08/LTG_CURL_OutdoorFishing_18.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x322/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" ezoid=\"0.3304620403242593\"><figcaption>Photo/Leatherman</figcaption></figure><h3>Feature Set</h3><ul><li>Closed Length: 4 in. (10 cm)</li><li>Primary Blade Length: 2.9 in. (7.37 cm)</li><li>Weight: 7.5 oz. (212 g)</li><li>Material: 100% stainless steel</li><li>Features: one-hand opening blade, removable pocket clip, outside-accessible features</li><li>Nylon sheath included</li></ul><figure id=\"attachment_268669\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-268669\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot.jpg\" alt=\"Leatherman's latest EC multi-tool\" width=\"2200\" height=\"1418\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot.jpg 2200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot-297x191.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot-800x516.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot-120x77.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot-768x495.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot-1536x990.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot-2048x1320.jpg 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot-696x449.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot-1068x688.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot-1920x1238.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot-652x420.jpg 652w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2200px) 100vw, 2200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot.jpg 2200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot-297x191.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot-800x516.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot-120x77.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot-768x495.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot-1536x990.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot-2048x1320.jpg 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot-696x449.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot-1068x688.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot-1920x1238.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18163134/Curl-Crab-Shot-652x420.jpg 652w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-268669\">Photo/Leatherman</figcaption></figure><h3>Built-In Toolkit</h3><ul><li>420HC knife</li><li>Awl with thread loop</li><li>Bottle opener</li><li>Can opener</li><li>Diamond-coated file</li><li>Hard-wire cutters</li><li>Large bit driver</li><li>Medium screwdriver</li><li>Needlenose pliers</li><li>Regular pliers</li><li>Ruler (8 in./19 cm)</li><li>Spring-action scissors</li><li>Wire cutters</li><li>Wire stripper</li><li>Wood/Metal file</li></ul><h2>Bit Kit Compatibility of the Leatherman Curl</h2><figure id=\"attachment_268865\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-268865\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083309/leatherman-curl-beauty.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083309/leatherman-curl-beauty.jpg\" alt=\"leatherman flat bit driver\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083309/leatherman-curl-beauty.jpg 600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083309/leatherman-curl-beauty-297x297.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083309/leatherman-curl-beauty-120x120.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083309/leatherman-curl-beauty-420x420.jpg 420w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083309/leatherman-curl-beauty.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083309/leatherman-curl-beauty.jpg 600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083309/leatherman-curl-beauty-297x297.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083309/leatherman-curl-beauty-120x120.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083309/leatherman-curl-beauty-420x420.jpg 420w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-268865\">The flat bit driver keeps the tool compact, but doesn’t allow for use of standard bits – without an adapter.</figcaption></figure><p>Bit kit compatibility means users can adapt the Curl multi-tool to their specific needs with add-ons from Leatherman’s accessories collection. One caveat to the bit compatibility is that to make this tool as compact as possible, Leatherman uses their own flat bits meaning you will have to buy the Leatherman Bit Kit Set rather than use standard 1/4″ bits.</p><figure id=\"attachment_268863\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-268863\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083140/leatherman-ratchet-driver-lifestyle-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083140/leatherman-ratchet-driver-lifestyle-1.jpg\" alt=\"Leatherman ratchet bit adapter\" width=\"768\" height=\"465\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083140/leatherman-ratchet-driver-lifestyle-1.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083140/leatherman-ratchet-driver-lifestyle-1-297x180.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083140/leatherman-ratchet-driver-lifestyle-1-120x73.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083140/leatherman-ratchet-driver-lifestyle-1-696x421.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083140/leatherman-ratchet-driver-lifestyle-1-694x420.jpg 694w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083140/leatherman-ratchet-driver-lifestyle-1.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083140/leatherman-ratchet-driver-lifestyle-1.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083140/leatherman-ratchet-driver-lifestyle-1-297x180.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083140/leatherman-ratchet-driver-lifestyle-1-120x73.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083140/leatherman-ratchet-driver-lifestyle-1-696x421.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083140/leatherman-ratchet-driver-lifestyle-1-694x420.jpg 694w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-268863\">Either the Ratcheting Driver or Bit Driver will make the Curl easier to use for bike adjustments and allow for standard 1/4″ bits.</figcaption></figure><p>However, there is a way around this if you puchase the Ratchet Driver accessory. This little device plugs into the flat bit driver on the multi-tool and allows for flat bits&nbsp;<em>or</em> standard 1/4″ bits to be used. It also extends the bit away from the tool body making it easier to get into tight spaces. Leatherman also sells a <a href=\"https://www.leatherman.com/bit-driver-extender-131.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">non-ratcheting Bit Extender</a> for $20 that also allows for use of 1/4″ bits. So if you’re planning on replacing your bike multi-tool with this, you are probably best off buying the tool and either the Ratchet Driver or Bit Driver Extender and picking up your choice of bits.</p><p>Currently, the brand offers two bike-geek friendly accessories, the <a href=\"https://www.leatherman.com/ratchet-driver-667.html?clickId=3668333028\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Ratchet Driver</a> ($30 MSRP) and the 42-bit <a href=\"https://www.leatherman.com/bit-kit-set-127.html?clickId=3668334255\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Bit Kit Set</a> ($25 MSRP).</p><h3>Ratchet Driver Adapter</h3><ul><li>3.26 in. (8.28 cm)</li><li>1.26 oz (35.7 g)</li><li>Magnetic bit holder (Leatherman flat bits or standard 1/4″ bits)</li><li>Three-way ratcheting (forward, reverse, locked)</li><li>Universal bit driver compatibility (fits pocket tools with large bit drivers)</li></ul><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083136/leatherman-bit-kit-set.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083136/leatherman-bit-kit-set.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083136/leatherman-bit-kit-set.jpg 600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083136/leatherman-bit-kit-set-297x297.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083136/leatherman-bit-kit-set-120x120.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083136/leatherman-bit-kit-set-420x420.jpg 420w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083136/leatherman-bit-kit-set.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083136/leatherman-bit-kit-set.jpg 600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083136/leatherman-bit-kit-set-297x297.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083136/leatherman-bit-kit-set-120x120.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20083136/leatherman-bit-kit-set-420x420.jpg 420w\"></a></p><h3>Bit Kit Set</h3